parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the driver is unable to regain control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the accelerator pedal sticks or becomes stuck
the engine RPMs increase suddenly
the vehicle fails to respond to braking
and the cruise control cable becomes jammed or stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control cable can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control cable becomes stuck or jammed
the accelerator pedal sticks or becomes stuck
the engine RPMs increase suddenly
and the vehicle fails to respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle body becomes stuck or jammed
the accelerator pedal sticks or becomes stuck
the engine RPMs increase suddenly
and the vehicle fails to respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and fracture of the subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit abnormal noises
vibrations
or shaking while driving
and the subframe may be visibly rusted or corroded. In some cases
the vehicle may suddenly stop or lose control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Front Subframe and Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front subframe and control arms can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel shakes or wobbles
the vehicle makes a loud noise or grinding sound
the control arm breaks or separates from the frame
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The bearing noise can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud noise or grinding sound
especially when driving at high speeds.
